This article is a press gaggle from Deputy Principal Press Secretary Josh Earnest and Secretary of Education Arne Duncan. They discuss the President's announcement at Mooresville Middle School regarding an education program. The program focuses on the importance of technology in education and the need for high-speed broadband in schools. Secretary Duncan emphasizes the economic competitiveness of this program and the need for the United States to be a leader in education. They also discuss the President's views on the recent leaks about the NSA's surveillance program. Finally, they briefly touch on the progress of the immigration reform bill in Congress.